args:
Guided by a friend's final words, Tobias travels
to a hidden village where he meets Nino, a girl
descended from Ilia. But when Paladyns of the
conservative sect come for her, Nino's charm
becomes armor that grants Tobias new power.
＂When there shall come a soul of light,\nthy gem shall shine and grant thee flight.＂
The birds have all the sky above to roam,\nbut I can only watch them.
I lack the wings to fly from this place, and\nalways will.
A Remote Region of South Grastaea
The note on the map said to ring the magic\nchime here...
A forest, out of thin air?! No... It must\nhave always been here. The chime's\npower has merely allowed me to see it.
I've never heard of magic on such a vast\nscale. Just what have you hidden here,\nSonniere?

The Scrolls of Perdition—an apocryphal text that
claims the Other was Ilia's child. Its contents split
the Southern Church in two. The perditionists hold
to its teachings while the conservatives deny them.
The two factions remain locked in war even now.

It was amid that conflict that I received a letter
from a neutral party—a priest and close friend—
asking to meet. But when I arrived at our
rendezvous point, a horrific scene unfurled
before me.
Sonniere?! You're bleeding!\nHold still, I'll wrap your wound!
Tobias... No. It's...too late... Take this.
It marks the...hidden village...\nThe chime...is the key...
Please... The noble blood... Nino...\nYou must...protect...Nino...
Who killed Sonniere, and to what end?\nWhat was this ＂noble blood＂ he spoke of?\nThe unanswered questions kept piling up.
But what I needed to do was crystal clear,\nif I was to carry out my late friend's final\nrequest.
So this is the hidden village?
Are you a resident? My name is Tobias. I\nam here at the priest Sonniere's behest.
Sonniere... So you're the next caretaker.
Well, your timing is good. Would you cut\nsome firewood? I'll go draw water from\nthe river.
Pardon? There appears to be a misunder—
After the wood's cut, you can clean out the\nbarn. We'll have lunch once you're done.
Ah, wait! Er... Not sure what I expected to\nfind here, but this wasn't it.
Good work. Food's almost ready.\nJust relax until then.
I haven't seen anyone else around.\nAre you the only one living here?
You weren't told? My parents died of\nillness years ago. It's just me now.
...Hm. Flavor's a little thin. Bring\nme the salt from that shelf there?
This? Done. Now, if you'd indulge me:\nwhat was your relationship with Sonniere?
None to speak of. He was a caretaker,\nnothing more. It was his job to hide us\nhere. Hand me those herbs?
Here. And what do you mean,\nhide you here?
It was your idea.\nYou lot at the Lineage Council.

After my family line lost the struggle for
succession, it was the Lineage Council
who told them they had to live in secrecy.
So ＂the noble blood wouldn't die out.＂
Please... The noble blood... Nino...\nYou must...protect...Nino...
Stew's ready. Let's eat while it's hot.
Sorry, I still haven't gotten your name.
Sonniere didn't even tell you that much?\nIt's Nino.
Nino... So you're the one he spoke of.
You've been acting very strange this whole\ntime. Did they really send you here without\ntelling you anything?
By the time I found him, Sonniere was... I\ndidn't get the chance to ask any questions.
Is the one called Nino here?!
Busy day... Don't recognize the voice.\nNot just anyone can get in here, though.\nFriend of yours?
Well, I'll go have a look. You eat.
(Seems Sonniere was working with others\nto take care of Nino's people.)
(She said they had no choice but to live\nhere in hiding... Why? And what is this\n＂Lineage Council＂ she mentioned?)
Remanding you to Church Headquarters.\nI would advise you to come quietly.
You've got a chime.\nAren't you with the Council?
This relic was confiscated from a heretical\nhigh priest brought before our inquisition.
The lies of the perditionists and that new\nsect have driven the South into chaos. This\ndesecration of the faith cannot be allowed.
What you call ＂faith＂ is just one arbitrary\nand selfish interpretation, same as anyone\nelse's.
Well, well. Tobias. So the perditionists\nare here as well.
Paladyn Goma. Just what do the\nconservatives want with this girl?
Our orders from the upper ranks state that\nshe is guilty of high blasphemy. Her toxic\nlies necessitate an accordant punishment.
Of the gravest sort. She claims to descend\nfrom the Goddess Ilia's own bloodline.
Our sects may differ in our beliefs, but this\nheresy is surely plain to any observer. Do\nnot meddle in this matter. Now come, girl.
Stop! Ow, you're hurting me! Let me GO!
Wait. If she is descended of the Goddess,\nwhat is her crime?
The faith's role is to protect. Attacking any\nwho profess different beliefs is nothing\nmore than tyranny done in faith's name.
You would call stifling the seeds of future\nstrife tyranny?
It is part of Ilia's teachings that all who\nlive deserve happiness.
This girl is a living being, no less than you\nor I. There can be no call to punish her\nwhen she has committed no crime.
If you would take her nonetheless,\nI cannot stand idly by and watch.
You would interfere with holy justice?\nThen we are left with little choice.\nMen, advance!
I suppose a Paladyn demands more than\ncommon knights. I'll handle this. The rest\nof you, protect my flank. HRAH!
We haven't crossed blades in some time.\nThe Milon Plains, was it? You've improved.
But my sword carries the weight of\nrighteousness behind it! GRAAAAAH!
Rrgh...! I've seen countless people abused\nin the name of faith.
I'll not turn a blind eye to any more!
(I've finally found one...\nA soul of light.)
My charm... The gem in it is glowing!
(I grant you the protection of my wing.\nWield it well.)
What are those strange vestments?!\nCould it be the Goddess's protection,\nbestowed to shield her true descendant?
That's not possible. The one true history\nmakes no mention of the Goddess Ilia ever\nbearing children.
Don't be unmanned by a simple change in\nattire! Fall upon him now, all of you!\nTobias dies here!
I have no shortage of questions,\nbut they shall have to wait.
My body feels light as a feather... Is this\nthe armor's power? With this, I can—!
Now, if you'll kindly unhand Nino.
